WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.199 --> 00:00:06.559
Today on our 2013 Chevy Silverado well be
installing the Curt hitch part number 14301.

00:00:06.559 --> 00:00:10.460
This is what our hitch will look like once
its installed.

00:00:10.460 --> 00:00:13.849
Next well go ahead and give you a couple measurements
to assist with selecting accessories for your

00:00:13.849 --> 00:00:15.049
new hitch.

00:00:15.049 --> 00:00:20.080
From the center of the hitch pin hole to the
outer most edge of the bumper is four inches.

00:00:20.080 --> 00:00:25.010
From the top of the receiver tube to the ground
is 18 and a half inches.

00:00:25.010 --> 00:00:29.210
This will assist you with selecting accessories
such as a draw bar, a bike rack, or a cargo

00:00:29.210 --> 00:00:30.210
carrier.

00:00:30.210 --> 00:00:31.980
Now lets go ahead with installation.

00:00:31.980 --> 00:00:36.570
Note weve already gone ahead and lowered and
removed the spare tire for the ease installation

00:00:36.570 --> 00:00:38.680
of the new hitch.

00:00:38.680 --> 00:00:41.810
Next well go ahead and point out the attachment
points.

00:00:41.810 --> 00:00:46.810
Well have a total of six attachment points,
three in each frame rail.

00:00:46.810 --> 00:01:03.489
This will be our forward, center, and 

00:01:03.489 --> 00:02:34.420
rear attachment point.

